A few nights ago my buddy @roaminrich asked me to be a guest on his weekly Route 66 show, 66 Minutes. I wanted to have a cool background and this is what I came up with. The motel sign is from the 66 town of Needles, CA. The S&H Green Stamps sign way in the background came from Bill Shea’s gas station museum on 66 in Springfield, IL. I’m not really an expert on anything but I love talking about this old road. Pretty much the only thing that rivals hot rods and racecars when it come to things I’m passionate about. @chels2104 even made a cameo and it was cool to include her too since she’s been on every 66 trip I’ve taken over the last four years. After the show was done I shoved everything out of the way and brought Frank’s sedan into his old shop. It’s home now, and this is where it’s gonna stay as long as I’m around. The link to the show is in my bio if you want to watch me bloviate. #hotrod #ford #modela #coupe #32 #1932 #deuce #1932ford #tudor #sedan #oldcar #classic #classiccars #vintage #vintagecars #neon #neonsign #neonlights #sign #route66 #historicroute66

First piece of neon is up in the new house. My signs and I have been relegated to the basement. I got a big fat NO from every woman in my life when it came to leaving that cool, 1930s watch repair sign over the mantle. That’s fine, the basement is almost 1000 sq feet, there’s a pool table, and I just ordered a ton of bamboo to start on my own private tiki lounge. By the time I get all of these signs hung up, @mortforts will have had a hand in fixing every one. He just finished up the barber shop sign and I handed him the Red Carpet Cleaners sign to fix the top half. He fixed a crack in the watch repair sign a few years ago, and my Lighthouse Lounge sign started smoking at the electrode the other day so it’ll be heading to @thebendsglassworks for repair as well. And I still need to find a place for my vintage window surround too. Down the road I’m going to try to build half a sign and mount it to the wall. Then Josh can fix and install the tubes from the former City Dairy in Auburn, MI that was about five minutes from our new place. #neon #neonsigns #neonlights #neonvibes #neonsign #advertising #sign #signage #signdesign #barbershop #watch #lounge #bar #tavern #divebar #cleaners #laundromat #basement #pool #billiards

When I first started hanging out with Frank Burrell, the guy who would alter my life in so many ways, he told me about his high school hot rod. The car was cool, but pretty typical of the day (around 1960) Model A coupe with a flathead V8. The story of how it got the V8 however was pretty incredible. Frank spent his childhood in Pennsylvania then moved to Michigan. Back in PA his grandfather drove Frank and the other kids to school in a 1946 Ford bus. That bus was eventually retired to his grandfather’s farm. When Frank turned 16 he acquired a bone stock ‘29 Model A coupe then proceeded to drive it from Oscoda, Michigan to has grandfather’s farm in Pennsylvania. When he got there he yanked the V8 out of the school bus then installed it in his A coupe. I’m not sure what he did for a transmission or how long it took, but he then hopped in his new AV8 coupe and drove back to Michigan. At 16, with no phone or gps, nothing! Frank’s son told me the engine died along the way and some sort of insulation or insulator in the distributor was the culprit. Frank fixed it with the gauze from a bandage and it made it 75 miles before he had to do it again. Luckily he had a box of bandages and repeated the procedure every two hours or so the rest of the way home. Yesterday his wife Sharon who sold me both of Frank’s’32 Fords and the house we now live in, stopped by and gave me a picture of that Model A. This is how it looked in high school when her and Frank were dating. Pretty neat. #hotrod #ford #history #modela #coupe #AV8 #oldcar #oldcars #classic #classiccars #classiccar #vintage #vintagecar #vintagecars #automotive #auto #automobile

Who wants a neat piece of agricultural history? This appears to be a F.E. Meyers orchard sprayer. It’s an early, pull behind model designed to be pulled by a tractor and it would’ve used a PTO to power the high pressure pump. Then a worker would’ve ridden on the platform in back or walked alongside and sprayed the trees. It rolls but it’s heavy. You’ll need a trailer with a winch or a bunch of friends. $450 located 15 minutes west of downtown Bay City, Michigan just off US-10 at the Mackinaw Road exit. #farmlife #farm #farming #relic #impliment #machinery #farmmachinery #farmimplements #farmequipment #orchard #history #tractor #vintage #yardart #agriculture #agriculturalhistory

Last weekend I headed to Eldora with some buddies to watch the World 100. Usually I drive 5 hours, watch the race, then head back home and I’m in bed by 6:00 am. This time we made a weekend out of it so we got to see some incredible racing Friday and Saturday. 900+ Horsepower and 2350 pounds, these cars are absolute animals. I grew up on pavement racing, I raced on paved tracks, but ever since I started coming to Eldora eight years ago, I’ve barely been to a paved track since. #worldofoutlaws #lucasoillatemodeldirtseries #eldora #ohio #dirttrack #dirttrackracing #latemodel #shorttrack #racing #automotive #stockcar #stockcarracing #racecars #speedway

Check out this monster. There’s a machining area of the shop that I really never messed with because it wasn’t mine, and I thought the previous owner might sell everything. Now that we own this place I’ve been slowly working on this section. There’s a Bridgeport, lathe, surface grinder, horizontal mill, drill presses, a Roll-In saw and this sucker that’s sat unused the entire time I knew Frank and the last eight years I’ve been out here. The other night I found a blade for it, cleared off 20 years of junk and grime from it, and got it running. It’s super slow, but it cuts really nicely. It’s a Clement B36 bandsaw first patented in 1892. This is the second model that came out around 1902 and ran till the early 1920s. So it’s at least 100 years old. I don’t know if Frank ever used it, but it’s really cool to see it functional again. I was really looking forward to getting rid of it, but now I think I’ll keep it in the rotation. #saw #bandsaw #machinery #old #oldtools #oldtoolsrule #vintage #vintagetools #vintagemachinery #vintagemachine #tools #shop

Holiday Nights at Greenfield Village is one of our favorite events. @chels2104 and I have been going for the last five years, but this year we were able to have dinner at the Eagle Tavern too. Really nice time in an incredible place. If you’re unfamiliar, Henry Ford acquired historic buildings from all around the country and built Greenfield Village next to his museum in Dearborn. It opened in 1929. We love visiting both places. If I could figure out a way to live at the museum I’d move in tomorrow. #history #america #americana #henryford #henryfordmuseum #museum #dearborn #michigan #modelt #automotive #automobile #auto #vintage #antique #antiqueauto #horses #christmas #christmasdecor #tavern #dinner #holidaynightsgreenfieldvillage

Cool early Christmas gift from @chels2104. We live about 20 minutes from Michigan’s Mid Century hot spot, Midland. There are so many MCM homes, businesses, civic buildings, and churches in this city, it’s just crazy. Many of which were designed by the man who lived here, Alden B. Dow. We weren’t allowed to take pictures of the interior, but I found a few pics online. This was also Dow’s studio, and when he met with prospective clients they gathered in the white block lobby. The floor actually sits a foot below a pond right outside the windows. Dow was a student and contemporary of FLW and you can see Wright’s influence like bringing nature into the living space, and the concept of Compression and release  throughout the house. By the time you reach the main living room you can walk out to a balcony that sits about ten feet over the water. We’re really fortunate to have places like this so close.
